				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: DoTs<a name="11466"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 27 03 1:37 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Ok, I want to try to clear things up for those of you who don't know how to make 5 dots stick.  The trick of it is, one or two dots will fall every tick. By twisting nonstop, you can actually stick the dot back on before the next tick pops up.  Sure, you get resists now and then, or you miss a note every once in a while, but the damage output is still higher than just twisting 4 in my experience, cause essentially you still get the damage from each of the 5 dots.
<br />

<br />
For those who want to go crazy with it, here's what you do if you get a resist / missed note in the middle somewhere.  Say your twist is like this:
<br />
Fire, Ice, Poison, Disease, Magic... let's say your Ice dot just doesn't land this time around... no sweat, just keep twisting like normal.  BUT replace the Magic (fufil's) with the Ice, and voila, slightly higher dmg output.  Of course, nothing says you won't get resisted again but it's worth a try right?  Any questions, comments, or complaints, bring em on.  I'm new to the message boards but I know my bard stuff  <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-5.gif" border="0" alt="Wink" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
Piemur Notebender
<br />
60 Punk of Prexus</span></td>
