			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: DoTs<a name="12720"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Dec 2 03 4:22 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>That makes pretty tricky twisting, Piemur. No offense meant though, if you can do it, better for you<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
Let's say you have the setup as follows:
<br />

<br />
1 fire, 2 ice, 3 poison, 4, disease, 5 magic.
<br />

<br />
So, if I understand well, you will be twisting the following order as long as you don't have any resists and missed notes:
<br />

<br />
1-2-3-4-5 <b>-</b> 1-2-3-4-5
<br />

<br />
But now you miss ice, and you say that you replace it by magic. You say, just replace magic with ice. Your twist then becomes:
<br />

<br />
1-x-3-4-2
<br />

<br />
But how do you continue? You haven't played magic, which has now dropped. And you aren't going to need to twist in ice again two ticks after you re-sang it, because it is far from having worn off yet. You could make your twist like this...
<br />

<br />
1-5-3-4-2
<br />

<br />
but see it suddenly becomes much more complicated? If you're good at memorizing the numbers of the new order it may work out for you though... but soon your twist may look like...
<br />

<br />
2-5-3-1-4
<br />

<br />
That is, anyway, how it would work if you try to keep up maximum efficiency. Otherwise I think it is a lot easier (and perhaps that is how you meant it all along) to do this:
<br />

<br />
1-2-3-4-5 <b>-</b> 1-x-3-4-2 <b>-</b> 1-2-3-4-5
<br />

<br />
You see that between the second and the third cycle the ice song is sung almost twice in a row...
<br />

<br />
Just some random thoughts (many of you may have already lost me by now, so maybe I'll just leave it at this).
<br />

<br />
Edit: Oh, one more thing, this is how I would twist, myself (and I don't do five songs). 'x' marks again a missed note. I don't resing resisted dots until the next cycle.
<br />

<br />
1-2-3-4 <b>-</b> 1-x-2-3 <b>-</b> 4-1-2-3 <b>-</b> 4-1-2-3</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
